To overcome the two problems here (client side loading the template and ending browser support) you could throw in php in the mix and have a wonderful solution for templating with bullet proof standards:
// XML
$xml_doc = new DOMDocument();
$xml_doc->load("file1.xml");// XSL
$xsl_doc = new DOMDocument(); $xsl_doc->load("file.xsl");// Proc
$proc = new XSLTProcessor();
$proc->importStylesheet($xsl_doc);
$newdom = $proc->transformToDoc($xml_doc);// Output
print $newdom->saveXML();XSLT lacks functionality? No problem, use php functions in xslt: https://www.php.net/manual/en/class.xsltprocessor.php
